    "correct": "**Surgical Mechanism:** Posterior urethral valves are congenital obstructive membranes within the male posterior urethra, distal to the external urethral sphincter. This obstruction leads to varying degrees of urinary stasis, hydronephrosis, bladder dysfunction, and potential renal damage. Antenatal diagnosis relies on sonographic detection of these sequelae, such as bilateral hydroureteronephrosis, a thickened bladder wall, a dilated posterior urethra (keyhole sign), and oligohydramnios, which are indirect but highly suggestive signs of the underlying urethral obstruction.\\n\\n**Clinical Execution:** Early antenatal detection of PUV-related findings allows for timely counseling, potential fetal intervention in severe cases (though controversial), and planned postnatal management. This proactive approach minimizes the progression of renal damage and optimizes outcomes by enabling prompt postnatal confirmation and intervention, such as valve ablation, before irreversible renal injury occurs.",
