    "R_review_learning_points": "**Conceptual Overview:** Maintenance fluid therapy in pediatrics aims to replace ongoing physiological losses of water and electrolytes and provide sufficient glucose to prevent hypoglycemia and ketosis. Calculations are weight-based, with careful consideration of age, clinical status, and potential ongoing abnormal losses. Over- or under-resuscitation can lead to severe electrolyte imbalances, fluid overload, or dehydration, particularly in the perioperative setting.\\n\\n| Weight Range | Daily Water (ml/kg) | Daily Na+ (mEq/kg) | Daily K+ (mEq/kg) |\\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\\n| 0-10 kg | 100 | 2-4 | 1-2 |\\n| 11-20 kg | 50 (for kg > 10) | 2-4 | 1-2 |\\n| >20 kg | 20 (for kg > 20) | 2-4 | 1-2 |\\n",
