    "visualization": "The surgeon must 'see' the precise numerical values for fluid volume, sodium, potassium, chloride, and dextrose concentration on the IV fluid order sheet, ensuring they align with the patient's weight and clinical status, rather than simply ordering 'D5 1/2 NS with 20K' without calculation."
