    "D": "Pure esophageal atresia (Type A) accounts for about 5-8% of cases. Both proximal and distal esophageal segments are blind, with a significant gap between them, and no tracheal connection. The stem would need to describe a gasless abdomen on X-ray (due to no air entering the stomach) and a large gap between esophageal pouches for this to be correct.",
