    "C": "The potassium requirement of 20meq is too low (2 meq/kg/day) compared to the standard 3 meq/kg/day for maintenance, potentially leading to hypokalemia. The stem would need to specify a patient with renal impairment or hyperkalemia risk to justify lower potassium.",
    "D": "The potassium requirement of 10meq is too low (1 meq/kg/day), risking hypokalemia. The dextrose requirement of 5gm is severely inadequate (0.5 gm/kg/day), leading to hypoglycemia and ketosis. The chloride requirement of 40meq is slightly high for maintenance. The stem would need to describe a patient with severe hyperkalemia and a need for minimal caloric intake.",
    "E": ""
