    "visualization": "When reviewing a patient's chart, the surgeon must 'see' the calculated fluid rate (e.g., 42 mL/hr for a 10kg infant), the specific fluid type (e.g., D5 1/4 NS), and the added potassium concentration (e.g., 20 mEq KCl/L) to confirm appropriate perioperative fluid orders."
