    "D": "This statement is medically accurate. Meckel's diverticulum is the most common congenital anomaly of the GI tract, a true diverticulum containing all layers of the intestinal wall, resulting from incomplete obliteration of the vitelline duct. If the question asked for a *correct* definition, this would be a strong contender.",
