    "C": "Surgical closure or embolization of the shunt is not universally indicated. The decision for intervention depends on the shunt type (Type I often not amenable to closure), the presence and severity of symptoms (e.g., hyperammonemia, hepatic encephalopathy, pulmonary hypertension), and the risk of complications. Asymptomatic Type II shunts may be managed with observation. The word 'always' renders this statement incorrect. For this option to be correct, it would need to specify 'Surgical closure is indicated for symptomatic Type II shunts amenable to intervention to prevent complications'.",
    "D": "Since options B and C are not alternative names for Abernethy malformation, 'All of the above' is incorrect.",
