    "takeaway": "Surgical intervention in NEC is indicated for intestinal perforation or clinical deterioration despite maximal medical therapy, always following initial resuscitation.",
    "visualization": "On abdominal X-ray, the surgeon must 'see' pneumatosis intestinalis (gas within the bowel wall), portal venous gas, or critically, free air under the diaphragm (pneumoperitoneum) indicating perforation, which mandates surgical intervention."
