    "D": "Hyperchloremia is incorrect; hypochloremia is a hallmark of pyloric stenosis due to loss of gastric HCl. For hyperchloremia to be correct, the infant would need to be receiving excessive chloride-containing fluids without significant gastric losses, or have renal tubular acidosis.",
    "E": ""
